JOHANNESBURG – Sixteen people have been injured in clashes between Mali’s security forces and opposition supporters during a prohibited march ahead of elections, AP reported. READ: Mali govt slams claims of live fire at protesters Opposition leaders organised Saturday’s march to call for free and transparent elections and for more state television coverage of their activities. The governor of the capital, Bamako, had banned the march under Mali’s state of emergency that was imposed in 2015 after an extremist attack on a local hotel. African News Agency